  "notes": "commit_sha intentionally left null per LANE_MANIFEST_SPEC.md sec4.2 (\"populated at merge\") and sec2 lifecycle table (Merge event sets commit_sha, not pre-merge pushes). No CI check reads this field pre-merge -- Return Review Packet resolves the live head directly from the pull_request event payload (github.event.pull_request.head.sha), never from the manifest. Chasing a self-referencing head SHA in this field pre-merge is structurally impossible (a commit cannot record its own SHA) and not required by any mechanical gate; the convention holds across other in-flight lanes (e.g. UTV2-1554 in_review) where commit_sha is stale relative to live PR head with no CI impact.",
